  // Buffalo²: z_{n+1} = |Re(z²)|+i|Im(z²)| + c.
  // Mandelbrot analogue — pixel = c, z₀ = 0.
  // The Buffalo fold applies absolute value to both components of z² after
  // the squaring: |Re(z²)|+i|Im(z²)| = |x²−y²|+i|2xy|. This bilateral fold
  // creates 2-fold rotational symmetry with four reflection axes (quadrant
  // symmetry). The parameter space has a rich interior near the fold boundary
  // with characteristic buffalo-horn curvature at the arm tips.
  // Smooth coloring: log₂(2) = 1. Supports normal-map shading (colorScheme 50-63).

